🧽 Behind the scenes of part of my Spongebob Reimagined piece (full vid on @spongebob ‘s YouTube channel) for @cartuna @nickelodeon @spongebob 

This scene was tricky with Patrick’s suit being blue, but his pants being green. Keying it properly meant taking a shot with blue background and green background and blending them in post. 
- @barwoodpumpkin did an incredible job making his tiny outfit for each frame. 
-I would reuse and transfer the muscles (and face) from the previous frame to each new one. 
-Using pulled felt instead of cutouts for the smear frames proved to be a good choice and are some of my favorite shots. 
-All the backgrounds were made separately to make life a little easier. 
(More behind the scenes to come)

Full behind the scenes/time lapse of my @blackpumas “Colors” claymation. Thanks again to @drmbear for helping this happen. 
Shot at 15fps in @dragonframe.software , made with Trail Mix clay from @georgiesceramic and animated over the course of 5 days. I started with the head first and then worked from there. Had to shoot the transition in and out (with the head) at the same time which was tricky. A lot of the shapes and movements of the clay were improvised to the music in real time. I had a basic concept, but wanted to keep it loose in case I had new ideas. I LOVE playing with this much clay. So fun. Thanks for watching. 
#stopmotion #stopmotionanimation #stopmotionvideo #animation #clay #claymation #blackpumas #sculpture #sculpt #pottery #ceramics #motion #motiondesign #musicvideo

Behind the scenes/alternate take of my claymation piece for @blackpumas “Colors” - big thanks to @drmbear for helping make this possible. Took about 5 days and used a lot of improvisation. 
Fun fact: a lot of us stop motion animators make “fake” behind the scenes time lapses where we pose our hands each shot to get a clean, exact time lapse with just the correct frames. I figured if I’m posing anyway might as well do something with my hands and make it more interesting. This is the result of that. People love hands! So I figure, make it fun. 
#stopmotion #stopmotionanimation #stopmotionvideo #claymation #animation #blackpumas #colors #sculpt #sculpture #ceramics #clay #pottery
